---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import HeroPreview from "../components/HeroPreview.astro";
---

<Base
  title="Latch"
  description="Latch triages your inbox before you read it — surfacing the four threads that need you today, archiving the rest, and writing the first draft. Built on Cloudflare."
>
  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="section hero">
    <div class="container hero-grid">
      <div class="hero-copy">
        <span class="eyebrow reveal reveal-1">Inbox triage for operators</span>
        <h1 class="reveal reveal-2">Wake up to four threads, not four hundred.</h1>
        <p class="lead reveal reveal-3">
          Latch reads your inbox while you sleep, surfaces the few threads that
          actually need you, drafts a reply for each one, and quietly archives
          the rest. You get your morning back. Your inbox stays at zero.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-cta reveal reveal-4">
          <a href="/pricing" class="btn btn-primary">Start free for 14 days</a>
          <a href="/features" class="btn btn-link">See how it works →</a>
        </div>
        <p class="hero-meta reveal reveal-4">
          <span class="dot"></span>
          Hosted on Cloudflare · Your inbox never leaves the edge
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-visual">
        <HeroPreview />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- LOGOS / SOCIAL PROOF -->
  <section class="section social">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="social-label">Used by operators at</p>
      <ul class="social-row" aria-label="Customer companies">
        <li>Mercury</li>
        <li>Linear</li>
        <li>Vercel</li>
        <li>Ramp</li>
        <li>Notion</li>
        <li>Cursor</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- THREE-UP VALUE PROPS -->
  <section class="section value">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow">Why Latch</span>
      <h2 class="value-h">An inbox shouldn't run your morning.</h2>
      <p class="lead value-sub">
        We built Latch for the people whose inbox is a queue of decisions, not
        conversations. Founders, heads of ops, chiefs of staff, on-call PMs.
        People who don't have time for "inbox zero" but can't afford to miss the
        one thread that matters.
      </p>

      <div class="value-grid">
        <article class="value-card">
          <h3>Triage that survives Monday.</h3>
          <p>
            Latch ranks every thread by who's waiting on you, what they're
            asking for, and how much it costs you to be late. The four threads
            that need you today rise to the top. Nothing else interrupts.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="value-card">
          <h3>A first draft for every reply.</h3>
          <p>
            For threads that need a response, Latch writes a draft in your
            voice, grounded in the last two months of how you've actually
            replied. You edit, you send. The blank page is gone.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="value-card">
          <h3>Quiet by default.</h3>
          <p>
            One morning summary email. No push notifications. No badge counts.
            No "Latch noticed…" interruptions. The whole point is that you
            stop checking.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- HOW IT WORKS — 3 steps -->
  <section class="section how">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow">How it works</span>
      <h2>Three minutes to set up. Two months of practice to feel native.</h2>

      <ol class="how-steps">
        <li>
          <span class="step-n">01</span>
          <h3>Connect your inbox.</h3>
          <p>Gmail OAuth, two clicks. Latch reads at the edge — your messages never sit on a third-party server.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="step-n">02</span>
          <h3>Spend a week saying yes / no.</h3>
          <p>For the first seven mornings, Latch shows its triage decisions and asks you to confirm. It learns your patterns fast.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="step-n">03</span>
          <h3>Get your morning back.</h3>
          <p>From week two onward, you wake to a summary of the four threads that need you, with drafts ready. The other 96% has already been handled.</p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA STRIP -->
  <section class="section cta-strip">
    <div class="container cta-row">
      <div>
        <h2>Try it tomorrow morning.</h2>
        <p class="lead">14 days free, no card. If Latch hasn't given you back an hour by Friday, cancel and we'll delete the model.</p>
      </div>
      <a href="/pricing" class="btn btn-primary">Start free</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .hero {
    padding-block-start: clamp(64px, 8vw, 112px);
    padding-block-end: clamp(64px, 8vw, 112px);
    background:
      radial-gradient(900px 360px at 90% -10%, rgba(84, 72, 230, 0.05), transparent 60%),
      var(--canvas);
  }
  .hero-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 7fr 5fr;
    gap: 48px;
    align-items: center;
  }
  @media (max-width: 920px) {
    .hero-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 40px; }
  }
  .hero-copy h1 { margin-block-end: 20px; }
  .hero-cta {
    margin-block-start: 28px;
    display: flex;
    gap: 18px;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .hero-meta {
    margin-block-start: 18px;
    color: var(--ink-3);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
  }
  .dot {
    display: inline-block;
    width: 6px; height: 6px;
    background: var(--success);
    border-radius: 50%;
  }
  .hero-visual { display: flex; justify-content: center; }

  .social { padding-block: 56px; }
  .social-label {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-3);
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 18px;
  }
  .social-row {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 40px;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .value-h { max-width: 22ch; margin-block-end: 16px; }
  .value-sub { margin-block-end: 48px; }
  .value-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 24px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 900px) { .value-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  .value-card {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: 28px;
  }
  .value-card h3 { margin-block-end: 10px; }
  .value-card p { color: var(--ink-2); }

  .how-steps {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin-block-start: 32px;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 24px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 900px) { .how-steps { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  .how-steps li {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    padding-block-start: 24px;
  }
  .step-n {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    color: var(--ink-3);
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
  }
  .how-steps h3 {
    margin-block-start: 12px;
    margin-block-end: 8px;
  }
  .how-steps p { color: var(--ink-2); }

  .cta-strip { background: var(--canvas-2); }
  .cta-row {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 40px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .cta-row h2 { margin-block-end: 8px; }
</style>
